- maybe done?



- how to do compositing:

	wrap a VipsImage around the large mem buffer the user passes in ...
	track the cod of the top left-corner of this image

	pass down to the tile reader

	if the tile we will read is exactly aligned with the buffer, we can do
	it zero-copy and read directly to the memory area

	otherwise, allocate a buffer, read to that, wrap an image around it,
	use vips_draw_image_direct() to render into the main image

	can do a transform before the vips_draw_image_direct() ... though we'd
	need to add a blending mode

	the wio_in check in vips_image_draw_direct() will render the image
	with threads, wooo






make aperio use vips instead of cairo 

	openslide-vendor-aperio.c

	read_tile() is the only function we call during decode which uses
	cairo ... it calls:

  cairo_surface_t *surface = cairo_image_surface_create_for_data(
   	(unsigned char *) tiledata,
	CAIRO_FORMAT_ARGB32,
	tw, th, tw * 4);
  cairo_set_source_surface(cr, surface, 0, 0);
  cairo_surface_destroy(surface);
  cairo_paint(cr);

	ie. paints pixels into cr at 0, 0

